properties.areaDesc: Two Rivers to Sheboygan WI; Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI; Sturgeon Bay to Two Rivers WI
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 17 at 10:24AM CST until January 19 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southeast winds 15 to 25 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt tonight. A lull in the gusty winds is expected
Saturday morning, then west winds will increase to 15 to 25 kt
with gusts to 35 kt late Saturday morning and afternoon. Waves
of 6 to 9 ft expected. For the Small Craft Advisory, southeast
winds 15 to 20 kt with gusts up to 25 kt, waves 3 to 6 ft
expected.

* WHERE...Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI, Sturgeon Bay
to Two Rivers WI and Two Rivers to Sheboygan WI.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 9 PM this evening to 3 AM
CST Sunday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 2 PM this
afternoon to 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 9 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 AM CST SUNDAY
